Web Service Endpoint# Delete a Bundle ID

App Store Connect API 1.1+## [URL](/documentation/AppStoreConnectAPI/DELETE-v1-bundleIds-_id_#url)



```
DELETE https://api.appstoreconnect.apple.com/v1/bundleIds/{id}
```

## [Path Parameters](/documentation/AppStoreConnectAPI/DELETE-v1-bundleIds-_id_#path-parameters)

`id``string` (Required) 

## [Response Codes](/documentation/AppStoreConnectAPI/DELETE-v1-bundleIds-_id_#response-codes)

` 204 No Content``No Content`

` 400 Bad Request``[ErrorResponse`](/documentation/appstoreconnectapi/errorresponse)`Bad Request`An error occurred with your request.

 Content-Type: application/json ` 401 Unauthorized``[ErrorResponse`](/documentation/appstoreconnectapi/errorresponse)`Unauthorized`

 Content-Type: application/json ` 403 Forbidden``[ErrorResponse`](/documentation/appstoreconnectapi/errorresponse)`Forbidden`Request not authorized.

 Content-Type: application/json ` 404 Not Found``[ErrorResponse`](/documentation/appstoreconnectapi/errorresponse)`Not Found`Resource not found.

 Content-Type: application/json ` 409 Conflict``[ErrorResponse`](/documentation/appstoreconnectapi/errorresponse)`Conflict`The provided resource data is not valid.

 Content-Type: application/json ` 429 ``[ErrorResponse`](/documentation/appstoreconnectapi/errorresponse)``

 Content-Type: application/json ## [Discussion](/documentation/AppStoreConnectAPI/DELETE-v1-bundleIds-_id_#Discussion)

You can only delete bundle IDs that are used for development. You can’t delete bundle IDs that are being used by an app in App Store Connect.
